This did not improve Bush's reputation, that said, objectively, he left his successor a much more favourable final situation than we could expect.
Barack Obama hopes that in Afghanistan, the miracle will reproduce
Again, it was the campaign commanders who asked for an increase in the military contingent, including the commander of the Afghan operation, General Stanley McCristal, who even severely criticized the house Blanche's reluctance despite the subordination habits.
