He managed to remove the additional 5,000 from Europe's promises, even though he had about 10,000 at the outset.
What brings the most problems to Obama's entire strategy seems to be his intention to remove the armies of Afghanistan in 18 months and to complete this whole process in three years' time. Obama's entire doctrine brings more questions than it does provide answers.
Many doubt the fact that a half increase will bring the same fruits as the progression in Iraq.
Despite the fratricidal wars of recent years, Iraqi society is relatively well organized and its leaders honor the agreements.
The Afghan situation is marked by the opposite - one cannot count on anyone and no treaty is respected.
Under these conditions, it is difficult to prepare Afghan security forces, who are used to changing their day-to-day leadership according to what arranges them.
Political institutions, although officially founded, will only remain from powder to the eyes behind which will proliferate patriarchal ethnic relations.
It is particularly complex to balance the interests of various ethnic groups in view of the lack of clarity in relation to reports, which are still complicated by Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Even the foundation of a "early state to act", which is the basic purpose of the operation, does not seem to be very real.
The temporal horizon of Obama's strategy makes his volunteerism perplexed.
In the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has only made it worse and is currently on the brink of chaos.
Only a purely romantic heart and out of reality can be persuaded that the small soldiers sent in the tumult of the war for their "early return to the house" will bring there a true miracle.
